caption.body: #Onthisday in 1988, the last branded PSA (Pacific Southwest Airlines) flight departed San Diego and landed in Las Vegas as an USAir flight. PSA was a San Diego based airline that began operating in 1949. With their discounted fares, easy check-ins, and friendly, on-time service, the airline had attracted a sizable, loyal customer base, which included businessmen, tourists and military personnel. What is your favorite PSA memory?  Image: Pacific Southwest Airlines (PSA) souvenir certificate, 1988. Gift of Thomas G. Dragges. 2015.168.706 - Pacific Southwest Airlines (PSA), Bae 146, flight attendant Carolyn Myers (left), c. 1981. Gift of Carolyn Myers.2010.114.020
